The project is currently on MSTest 3.8.0. The user says they're upgrading to MSTest 4.x and getting CS1615 errors on the `out` parameter in `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>(obj, out var typed)`.

In MSTest v4, the `out` parameter was removed from `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>`. Instead, the method now returns the typed value directly:

```csharp
// Before (v3)
Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>(obj, out var typed);

// After (v4)
var typed = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>(obj);


```

Now I need to update all three occurrences of this pattern in the codebase, bump the package version, and verify everything builds and runs correctly.

